1. Python Implementation

This script uses the requests library to fetch live odds for upcoming games. You will need an API key from The Odds API.

Python
import requests

# 1. Configuration
API_KEY = 'YOUR_API_KEY'
SPORT = 'upcoming' # Use 'soccer_epl', 'americanfootball_nfl', etc.
REGION = 'us'      # us | uk | eu | au
MARKET = 'h2h'    # h2h (moneyline) | spreads | totals
ODDS_FORMAT = 'american' # decimal | american

# 2. Get Odds Data
odds_response = requests.get(
    f'https://api.the-odds-api.com/v4/sports/{SPORT}/odds', 
    params={
        'api_key': API_KEY,
        'regions': REGION,
        'markets': MARKET,
        'oddsFormat': ODDS_FORMAT,
    }
)

if odds_response.status_code != 200:
    print(f'Error: {odds_response.status_code}, {odds_response.text}')
else:
    odds_json = odds_response.json()
    print(f'Successfully fetched {len(odds_json)} events')
    
    # Print the first event's odds
    if odds_json:
        print(f"Match: {odds_json[0]['home_team']} vs {odds_json[0]['away_team']}")
        print(f"Bookmaker: {odds_json[0]['bookmakers'][0]['title']}")
2. Node.js (JavaScript) Implementation

Using the axios library, this is ideal for web applications or backend services.

JavaScript
const axios = require('axios');

const apiKey = 'YOUR_API_KEY';
const sportKey = 'upcoming';

axios.get(`https://api.the-odds-api.com/v4/sports/${sportKey}/odds`, {
    params: {
        apiKey: apiKey,
        regions: 'us',
        markets: 'h2h,spreads',
        oddsFormat: 'american',
    }
})
.then(response => {
    console.log(JSON.stringify(response.data, null, 2));
    console.log('Remaining Requests:', response.headers['x-requests-remaining']);
})
.catch(error => {
    console.log('Error:', error.response ? error.response.data : error.message);
});
Key Features & Parameters

If you are trying to replicate the Sports Odds Plus experience, these parameters are essential:

Parameter	Options	Description
regions	us, us2, uk, eu, au	Filters bookmakers by geographic region.
markets	h2h, spreads, totals, outrights	Defines the type of betting lines returned.
oddsFormat	decimal, american	Sets the visual format of the price.
eventIds	(Comma separated IDs)	Filters the response to specific matches only.
